2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on multi-cell networks and resource allocation, which are key topics in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper discusses user clustering and power allocation, which are relevant to social and information networks. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper mentions efficiency gains, which could be related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper discusses optimization approaches and convergence guarantees, which are relevant to game theory.
